ASTAP++ — Database and third-party acknowledgements
====================================================

ASTAP++ is a C++23 port of ASTAP (Astrometric STAcking Program) by Han
Kleijn, www.hnsky.org. Database acknowledgements below follow the
original ASTAP documentation.


deep_sky.csv
------------

A free-to-use deep-sky database of 30,000 objects for non-commercial
use only, compiled by Han Kleijn between 1997 and 2020 for the Hallo
Northern Sky program and ASTAP, based heavily on:

- SAC81, Saguaro Astronomy Club Database v8.1 (March 22, 2010), Steve
  Coe, database manager. https://www.saguaroastro.org/sac-downloads

- Wolfgang Steinicke's Revised NGC & IC.
  http://www.klima-luft.de/steinicke/index_e.htm
  Non-commercial use is free but the author requests notification.
  Commercial use requires prior contact. A proper acknowledgement of
  the source, including an answer-back to the author, is necessary
  in all cases.

- HyperLeda — see separate entry below.

- Sh2 — Sharpless S. 1959, "A catalogue of HII regions",
  ApJS 4, 257-279. 1959ApJS....4..257S

- vdB — Van den Bergh S. 1968, "A study of reflection nebulae",
  AJ 73, 233-245. 1968AJ.....73..233R

- HCG — Nolthenius R. 1993, "A revised catalog of CfA1 galaxy groups
  in the Virgo/Great Attractor flow field", ApJS 85, 1-25.
  1993ApJS...85....1N

- LDN — Lynds B.T. 1962, "Catalogue of dark nebulae", ApJS 7, 1-52.
  1962ApJS....7....1L

- PK — Kohoutek L. and Kuhl D. 2002, "Accurate coordinates of
  planetary nebulae", AN 323, 484-487. 2002AN....323..484K

- SIMBAD Astronomical Database, Centre de Données astronomiques de
  Strasbourg, was heavily used in the compilation.


variable_stars.csv
------------------

Selection from GCVS, the General Catalogue of Variable Stars,
version 5.1, by Samus N.N., Kazarovets E.V., Durlevich O.V.,
Kireeva N.N., and Pastukhova E.N.
Astronomy Reports, 2017, vol. 61, No. 1, pp. 80-88. 2017ARep...61...80S
Compiled 2019-6-6.


hyperleda.csv
-------------

Extract from the HyperLEDA database, http://leda.univ-lyon1.fr

HyperLEDA is a collection of homogenised measurements of galaxies,
maintained by the Observatoire de Lyon (France) and the Special
Astrophysical Observatory (Russia). All data and software are publicly
available under open-source terms for non-commercial use.

- Paper: Makarov et al., 2014, A&A 570, A13.
  http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2014A%26A...570A..13M
- "We acknowledge the usage of the HyperLeda database,
   http://leda.univ-lyon1.fr"


D05, D20, D50, V50, G05 star databases
--------------------------------------

Extracts from the Gaia star catalog release DR3 by the European Space
Agency (ESA), in a special format developed for the HNSKY planetarium
program and ASTAP.

